<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">07 — Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Built-in refrigerator repair — what LA homeowners ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does built-in refrigerator repair cost in Los Angeles?</h3>
        <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Sensors, valves, fan motors: $200–$400. Control board: $350–$650. Compressor: $600–$1,200+. For a $15,000 Sub-Zero, even a $1,200 repair is 8% of replacement cost — repair almost always makes sense.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My Sub-Zero isn't cooling — what should I check first?</h3>
        <p>Clean the vacuum condenser through the front kick grille. Clogged condenser is the most common "not cooling" cause on Sub-Zero built-ins. If cleaning doesn't restore normal operation within 24 hours, call us — it's a compressor or sealed system issue.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Is it worth repairing a Sub-Zero or Miele vs replacing it?</h3>
        <p>Almost always yes. These refrigerators are built for 20+ year service lives. A $800 repair on a $15,000 Sub-Zero is straightforward. Even a $1,200 sealed system repair on an 18-year-old unit beats $15,000+ for a replacement. We give you the repair cost upfront — but for quality built-ins, repair wins the math virtually every time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is Sub-Zero's dual compressor and why does it matter?</h3>
        <p>Sub-Zero is the only brand with two independent compressors — one for the refrigerator section, one for the freezer. This means which section is warm tells you exactly which compressor has failed. Refrigerator warm + freezer fine = refrigerator compressor. It's a diagnostic advantage that only exists on Sub-Zero.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair panel-ready and integrated refrigerators without damaging the cabinetry?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Panel-ready and fully integrated models require careful handling to avoid contacting the custom cabinetry panel surface. Our technicians are experienced with Sub-Zero integrated, Miele integrated, and Thermador panel-ready configurations — these are standard service calls for us in Beverly Hills, Bel Air, and Brentwood kitchens.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

